column32: Greetings, adventurer. I deal in the issuing of guildleves.
column33: My apologies, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>ma'am<Else/>sir</If>, but I am not authorized to issue guildleves to those as new to adventuring as you appear to be.
column34: The quest you were assigned is of the utmost import. May the Matron see you to success.

column32: If it is a guildleve you seek, then I may just have the right one for you.
column33: My records show that you have only recently arrived in Eorzea. I am sorry, but I cannot entrust you with the responsibility of a levequest until you have proven yourself to at least <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi</Case></Switch> of the Adventurers' Guild.
column34: Good luck, and may the Twelve be with you.
column35: My records show that you have only recently arrived to the area. I am sorry, but I cannot entrust you with the responsibility of a levequest until you have proven yourself to at least <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi</Case></Switch> of the Adventurer's Guild.
column36: Let me see here... Ah, yes. Our levewatches report that you completed all leve objectives within the allotted time. Well done, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>! Let me ready your reward.
column39: It addition to the objectives, it also seems you have found the time to slay a wanted target. Well done, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>! The bounty is yours!

column32: Here fer the leves, are ye? Well, then ye come to the right place. I has leves comin' out me arse...er, figuratively speakin', of course.
column33: Here fer the leves, are ye? Well, then ye come to the wrong place. You ain't straight with <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi</Case></Switch>, you ain't straight with me. Now git, afore I call me a Wailer.
column34: Luck of the Spinner to ye, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If>.
column35: Here fer the leves, are ye? Well, then ye come to the wrong place. Ye don't look as if ye could stand yer ground against a squirrel, let alone the beasties we has lurkin' in these woods. Now git yer green arse back to grindin' afore the diremites find ye. Heh heh heh!
column36: Back already, are ye? I suppose ye'll be wantin' yer reward now.
column39: Watches tell me ye went and stuck ye a wanted target, to boot. I suppose ye'll be wantin' the bounty with yer reward, then, eh?

column32: There is work to be had, if you are interested, my friend.
column33: I have no work for you, adventurer. Hone your skills, and then come and see me again once <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi</Case></Switch> of the Adventurer's Guild has deemed you worthy.
column34: Do not stray from duty, adventurer. I suggest seeing to the tasks at hand immediately.
column35: I have no work for you, adventurer. Hone your skills, and then come and see me again once you've proven you can stand your ground against the creatures roaming these parts.
column36: Your performance was noted by the local levewatches. I shall prepare your reward accordingly.
column39: And do not fret. The bounty for the wanted creature you slew has been added.

column32: The people of the Twelveswood need your help, adventurer. Have you the courage to provide it?
column33: The people of the Twelveswood are always looking for those willing to assist them. Unfortunately, you still look a tad green to be of any real help. Now if <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>someone such as Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>someone such as Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> were to vouch for you, that would be a different story...
column34: The quest you were assigned is of the utmost import. May the Matron see you to success.
column35: The people of the Twelveswood are always looking for those willing to assist them. Unfortunately, you still look a tad green to be of any real help. Now if <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>someone such as Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>someone such as Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> were to vouch for you, that would be a different story...
column36: Well done, adventurer. The levewatch overseeing your duty was thoroughly impressed. You may take your reward.
column39: Oh, and I have seen to it that the bounty of the wanted target you most bravely slew was included.

column32: Welcome, welcome! The people of the Black Shroud are in desperate need of a <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> of your talents. Might I interest you in a leve or two?
column33: Welcome, welcome! The people of the Black Shroud are in constant need of a helping hand. Might you know of anyone talented in the arts of battle or spellcraft? You? Oh no, <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> would have my head on a platter if I were to allow one as green as you take on the tasks I've been entrusted.
column34: Godsspeed to you then!
column35: Welcome, welcome! The people of the Black Shroud are in constant need of a helping hand. Might you know of anyone talented in the arts of battle or spellcraft? You? Oh no, the guildmaster would have my head on a platter if I were to allow one as green as you take on the tasks I've been entrusted.
column36: Excellent. The levewatches have reported, and I have used their evaluation to tally your reward.
column39: The extra gil you see included is the bounty for the wanted target you slew.

column32: Greetings, adventurer. I deal in the issuing of guildleves.
column33: My apologies, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>ma'am<Else/>sir</If>, but I am not authorized to issue guildleves to those as new to adventuring as you appear to be. Perhaps you should <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>return to Limsa Lominsa and speak with Baderon Tenfingers of the Drowning Wench</Case><Case(2)>return to Gridania and speak with Mother Miounne of the Carline Canopy</Case><Case(3)>speak with Momodi Modi across the hall</Case></Switch> and see if she cannot point you in the right direction.
column34: May the Traders see you to fortune.
column35: My apologies, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>ma'am<Else/>sir</If>, but I am not authorized to issue guildleves to those as new to adventuring as you appear to be. It might serve you well to step outside the city walls and see the world before running headlong into tasks that will only put your precious life in danger.
column36: I take it the quest was a success. Or, at least that is what the levewatches tell me. I have your reward right here.
column39: Ah, and the extra coin─that is the bounty you earned by slaying the wanted target. The Brass Blades extend their gratitude for your service to the sultanate.

column32: The realm is always in need of eager volunteers to tend to those tedious tasks which need tending. You have a certain air of eagerness about you. Try your hand at a levequest?
column33: You appear eager to serve the realm. This is good! Unfortunately, you do not appear to be of body <Emphasis>or</Emphasis> mind to serve her that well. This is bad. Speak with <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi</Case></Switch> to see if there is any way we might loosen this knotty situation we find ourselves in.
column34: For coin and country!
column35: You appear eager to serve the realm. This is good! Unfortunately, you do not appear to be of body <Emphasis>or</Emphasis> mind to serve her that well. This is bad. Whet you blade...or bow, or staff, or whatever may be your weapon of choice on some of the poor creatures crawling about the area and speak to me again when you are ready to take on the world...or at least the world immediately outside the city walls.
column36: The levewatches were impressed, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>! Here is your well-earned reward!
column39: Oh, and don't let me forget this bounty. That was a noble display out there!

column32: Good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> to you, adventurer. And a fine <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> it is, I say. A fine <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> for a levequest!
column33: Good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> to you, adventurer. And a fine <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> it is, I say. A fine <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> to march back to the Adventurers' Guild in <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Limsa</Case><Case(2)>Gridania</Case><Case(3)>Ul'dah</Case></Switch> and set yourself straight with <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch>. Only then will I let you partake in some of these fine guildleves I hold here.
column34: Off you are then! Time is of the essence!
column35: Good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> to you, adventurer. And a fine <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> it is, I say. A fine <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> to march back out into the field  Only then will I let you partake in some of these fine guildleves I hold here.
column36: I see the desert heat wasn't too much for you. Here is your reward. See that you don't spend it all at the pub!
column39: Oh, and the bounty! It almost slipped my mind. I believe you'll be wanting this, as well. Unless, that is, you don't, because I would be more than happy to─ You <Emphasis>do</Emphasis> want it, then. Alright. I suppose that's only fair, considering <Emphasis>you</Emphasis> were the one who killed the fiend.

column32: A lonely place, this Swiftperch. That don't mean there ain't work to be done.
column33: A lonely place, this Swiftperch. That don't mean there ain't work to be done...just not by the likes of an unbloodied fry like yerself. 'Til <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>ol' Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>wee Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> hasn't signed off on ye, I'll entrust the safety of this godsforsaken corner of the realm to more capable hands.
column34: I've me eye on ye and all, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If>. See the job's done right, like.
column35: A lonely place, this Swiftperch. That don't mean there ain't work to be done...just not by the likes of an unbloodied fry like yerself. 'Til ye've shown ye can hold yer own, I'll entrust the safety of this godsforsaken corner of the realm to more capable hands.
column36: A fair lick, that were. Let me ready yer coin now, so as ye can be on yer way.
column39: Ah, but not afore ye take this bounty. I saw what ye did up there to the wanted cur, like. Not flayt, were ye?

column32: I suppose you're here lookin' for some leves. Well, take your pick. But be quick about it. I haven't all day.
column33: Let me ask you someaught. Do you like this hat? I like this hat. It took me ten summers of lickin' ol' Baderon's boot to get this hat─a <Emphasis>levemete's</Emphasis> hat. I'd like to keep this hat, and doin' so means I's got to follow the rules. And rule number one? No leves to those what ain't proved them sen. Now back to the Adventurers' Guild with you.
column34: Best of luck to you, then. If I'm not here when you get back, might be I'm in the pub.
column35: Let me ask you someaught. Do you like this hat? I like this hat. It took me ten summers of lickin' ol' Baderon's boot to get this hat─a <Emphasis>levemete's</Emphasis> hat. I'd like to keep this hat, and doin' so means I's got to follow the rules. And rule number one? No leves to those what ain't proved them sen. Now back out into the bloody battlefields with you.
column36: You'll not get a single gil from me while the leve's─ Hold on a tick... The levewatch tells me all is right as rain. I'll ready your reward.
column39: Then there's the wee matter of this bounty. I reckon you'll be lookin' to claim it.

column32: You look to be of able mind and body. Might I interest you in a guildleve?
column33: I sense a certain weakness of both body and mind. I cannot assign a guildleve to one such as yourself. Perhaps good Mother Miounne has a task or two with which you might prove your skills.
column34: The spirits are ever watching, my friend. Prove to them you are worthy of the duty you have been entrusted.
column35: I sense a certain weakness of both body and mind. I cannot assign a guildleve to one such as yourself. Perhaps you might prove your skills on some lesser foes before attempting to take on those which lurk nearby.
column36: You return in one piece, so I can only assume that the spirits approve of your deeds. Allow me to prepare your reward.
column39: And what is this? A little bird tells me that you have dispatched a wanted villain. That would make this bounty yours, as well.

column32: The people here need any and all help that happens their wise. Might you be here to lend your blade?
column33: The people of Little Ala Mhigo are in dire need of aid, but only from those with the capacity to give it. <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> will decide whether or not you are worthy. I suggest speaking with <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>him</Case><Case(2)>her</Case><Case(3)>her</Case></Switch> if you ever wish to embark on a levequest.
column34: May you return unharmed.
column35: The people of Little Ala Mhigo are in dire need of aid, but only from those with the capacity to give it. Prove you have that capacity in the field first if you ever wish to embark on one of our levequests.
column36: You appear none the worse for wear. This reward should help lift your spirits.
column39: As will this bounty for the wanted target you put down. A true menace, that character was.

column32: You have the air of a <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> who has seen <If(PlayerParameter(4))>her<Else/>his</If> share of adventure. If you are interested, I may have the perfect job for you.
column33: I am Merthelin of the Adventurers' Guild. I am tasked with meting out guildleves to those who have proven themselves to guildmaster <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch>...of which you have not.
column34: Make you preparations quickly and proceed with the task at hand. Your clients will be awaiting word of your success.
column35: I am Merthelin of the Adventurers' Guild. I am tasked with meting out guildleves to those with the capacity to face the creatures of Tranquil Paths and return with their lives...of which you do not seem to possess.
column36: Your work today is commendable. I shall see you recompensed at once.
column39: Indeed, you have gone above and beyond the call of duty, what with slaying that wanted dastard. Here, the bounty is yours to take.

column32: Western Thanalan needs your help. Are you <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> enough to give it?
column33: Western Thanalan needs your help, but I've seen more worthy tumbleweed roll through the Crossing. You should climb your way back to the Adventurers' Guild and make yourself known to the guildmaster. Once I have the approval of the guild, then I might be able to accommodate you with a leve or two.
column34: Good luck and godsspeed!
column35: Western Thanalan needs your help, but I've seen more worthy tumbleweed roll through the Crossing. You should step out from behind the your mummy's frillies and bloody that weapon of yours. Once I find you fit, then I might consider entrusting you with a leve or two.
column36: I see you are still with us in the realm of Nald. Thal will be disappointed, but he always is. Here is your reward.
column39: And with it, the bounty you earned for slaying that wanted target. Impressive work, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. Quite impressive.

column32: Here for work, are you? You and everyone else, it seems. Good thing we have a lot of it.
column33: Here for work, are you? You and everyone else, it seems. The only difference being that they have been approved by <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon Tenfingers</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> of the Adventurers' Guild, and you have not.
column34: See to it then.
column35: Here for work, are you? You and everyone else, it seems. The only difference being that they have been approved by me, and you have not. How does one get approval, you ask? Killing, maiming, disemboweling, rending, cleaving, culling. The usual.
column36: The levewatches have reported and I've adjusted your pay accordingly. No complains, you hear? I get enough from the two mummers flanking me.
column39: Oh, and the bounty. You didn't think I would forget, did you? Did you?

column32: Another adventurer, eh? A man can move to the very edge of the realm and he'll still bump into one of your kind. I suppose it's not all bad, though. Especially when there are leves to be done.
column33: Used to be a 'Cuda. Manned the camp right beyond Limsa... Manned it that is, 'til I lost my big toe. A chunk of Dalamud fell straight on it. Consider myself lucky, though. Another ilm to the left, I'd have lost a lot more than that. Now, as for you... I've no leves for you. <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch>'s orders. Haul your arse back to the Adventurers' Guild if you've a problem with that.
column34: Till the sea swallows you! Gah hah hah!
column35: Used to be a 'Cuda. Manned the camp right beyond Limsa... Manned it that is, 'til I lost my big toe. A chunk of Dalamud fell straight on it. Consider myself lucky, though. Another ilm to the left, I'd have lost a lot more than that. Now, as for you... I've no leves for you. <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch> made it clear I'm to issue no quests to those without at least a few scars to prove their worth.
column36: Look who's returned all giddy as a gil turtle. Now take the coin and be off with you.
column39: And one last thing before you go─your share of the bounty. Unless you think I should keep it? Gah hah hah!

column32: Well met. Let us find a leve that suits your talents.
column33: The Adventurers' Guild has strict rules on who can and cannot partake in levequests. You fall in the latter half, as you have not received specific permission from guildmaster <Switch(IntegerParameter(1))><Case(1)>Baderon</Case><Case(2)>Mother Miounne</Case><Case(3)>Momodi Modi</Case></Switch>.
column34: May the Navigator guide you!
column35: The Adventurers' Guild has strict rules on who can and cannot partake in levequests. You fall in the latter half, as you have yet to prove yourself capable of handling the type of tasks I offer. Hone your skills in battle, and I may reconsider.
column36: You were quick to return. The levemetes have only just reported your accomplishments. Allow me a moment to prepare your reward.
column39: And here is the bounty for the wanted target. It would be a shame if your efforts went unrecognized.

column32: I am Storm Sergeant First Class Eugene Rivers, charged with the issuing of Grand Company levequests.
column33: I am not authorized to issue quests to those who have yet to prove themselves to the realm. Perhaps you should try your hand at several guildleves from the local Adventurers' Guild.
column34: [MacroError]
column35: I am not authorized to issue quests to those who have yet to prove themselves to the realm. Perhaps you should try your hand at several guildleves from the local Adventurers' Guild.
column36: [MacroError]
column37: Someone high up believed that it would be a fine idea to allow members from any Grand Company accept leves meant for the Maelstrom. I personally do not agree, but I have my orders. They did <Emphasis>not</Emphasis> mention aught of allowing those adventurers who had yet to pledge their allegiance to even the lowly Order of the Twin Adder, let alone the mighty Maelstrom.

column32: Storm Sergeant First Class C'lafumyn Quoh. I have been given authorization to issue Grand Company levequests.
column33: I will not issue Grand Company levequests to those who have not even completed a single leve for the Adventurers' Guild.
column34: May the Navigator Guide you, <WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComSea')><WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComFst')><WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComWil')> <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,2)/>!
column35: I will not issue Grand Company levequests to those who have not even completed a single leve for the Adventurers' Guild.
column36: [MacroError]
column37: You do not appear to be affiliated with any of the Grand Companies of Eorzea. The leves I issue are only for those who have pledged to serve the realm.
column38: I cannot issue company levequests to those who have not attained the rank of Sergeant Third Class. I have my orders.

column32: My duty within the Order of the Twin Adder is to issue Grand Company levequests.
column33: You shall not be issued a single company leve until you have proven you can handle one issued by the Adventurers' Guild.
column34: [MacroError]
column35: You shall not be issued a single company leve until you have proven you can handle one issued by the Adventurers' Guild.
column36: [MacroError]
column37: I have no leves for you, civilian. Enlist yourself in a Grand Company─preferrably the Order of the Twin Adder─and then speak with me again.

column32: The Order of the Twin Adder has tasked me with the issuance of Grand Company levequests.
column33: You must accept my apologies, but I must turn you away. You see, I cannot issue Grand Company leves to those who put themselves before the realm. Show your commitment to the aid of Eorzea's children by first accepting their tasks. The Adventurers' Guild will steer you true.
column34: The Matron ever watches, <WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComSea')><WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComFst')><WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComWil')> <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,2)/>.
column35: You must accept my apologies, but I must turn you away. You see, I cannot issue Grand Company leves to those who put themselves before the realm. Show your commitment to the aid of Eorzea's children by first accepting their tasks. The Adventurers' Guild will steer you true.
column36: [MacroError]
column37: The Order of the Twin Adder has tasked me with the issuance of Grand Company levequests. They have also tasked me with turning away all those who have yet to enlist. Consider yourself turned away.
column38: You must accept my apologies, but I must turn you away. You see, I cannot issue leves to those who have not proven their worth. Speak with me again upon attaining the rank of Sergeant Third Class.

column32: The name is Kikiri Kiri, but you can call me Sergeant Kiri. It's my duty to issue company leves, and you tell them I do a right fine job of it, if anyone asks.
column33: No company leves for you, I'm afraid. The Adventurers' Guild hasn't given you their official stamp of approval, and you won't find me questioning any one of the guildmasters' judgment.
column34: [MacroError]
column35: No company leves for you, I'm afraid. The Adventurers' Guild hasn't given you their official stamp of approval, and you won't find me questioning any one of the guildmasters' judgment.
column36: [MacroError]
column37: No company leves for you, my friend. The Immortal Flames are required by allied decree to offer levequests to those belonging to lesser companies, namely the Maelstrom and the Order of the Twin...something or other, but nowhere does it state that we need to provide leves to common riff-raff.

column32: Flame Sergeant First Class Eager Raptor. I suppose you're here to be issued a Grand Company levequest.
column33: The commanding officer would have my head on a pike if I were to allow one who had yet to complete even the simplest of guild-issued levequests to undertake one of our tasks.
column34: May you walk in the light of the crystal, <WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComSea')><WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComFst')><WARNING: unknown macro code ('ifComWil')> <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,2)/>.
column35: The commanding officer would have my head on a pike if I were to allow one who had yet to complete even the simplest of guild-issued levequests to undertake one of our tasks.
column36: [MacroError]
column37: Apologies, adventurer. I am only authorized to issue leves to those who have enlisted in a Grand Company. You have not, and here we stand.
column38: The commanding officer would have my head on a pike if he knew I'd issued a leve to someone who hadn't even earned the rank of Sergeant Third Class.
